# --- Type/Array GET: ToObjectFromJson<T>() doesn't support complex element types ---
# Typed convenience method returns use ToObjectFromJson<IReadOnlyList<T>>() which
# works for primitives (int, string, float, bool, DateTimeOffset) but fails for:
# - TimeSpan: ISO 8601 duration format not supported by default JSON serializer
# - Model: Internal parameterless constructor not accessible to JsonSerializer
# - BinaryData: Not JSON-serializable
# Fix: Use JsonDocument.Parse + element-level deserialization for these types.
DurationValueGet
ModelValueGet
NullableModelValueGet
UnknownValueGet

